reviews/2/text:
Fiquei desapontada porque pensei que poderíamos ver a casa deste poeta o mais semelhante possível com o que seria na época. Talvez com tudo colocado como ele teria na altura e materiais que usava, o seu escritório, a sala onde tinha os convidados, etc (como se se tratasse mesmo de uma visita à sua casa). Em vez disso o museu está contido numa pequena divisão e tem uma cronologia (impressa em cartolinas) com alguns dos eventos mais importantes da vida e da época do poeta. 

É uma visita muito rápida e barata, mas diria que não vale muito a pena. Talvez só para ir uma vez. No andar de cima está então um pequeno museu/sala de arquivo com fotos e material de trabalho de um conhecido fotógrafo setubalense; Américo Ribeiro. Foi mais interessante, sem dúvida.
reviews/2/title: Pequena sala com informações em cartolina...
reviews/3/text: Casa pequena e exposição simples de um homem e poeta tão grande,mostra apenas um pouco do muito que foi.Recomendo.
reviews/4/text:
Uma exposição pequena e bem simples sobre este grande poeta.
Bem escondida e acessível por mapa ou celular.
reviews/5/text: Tendo em conta a grandiosidade deste poeta e a homenagem que pela cidade lhe é prestada, tal como denominar praças, padarias, barbearia, entre outros locais com o seu nome, a sua casa oferece-nos apenas uma pequena introdução ao que foi a sua vida. Apesar de parte desta ser uma incógnita, a casa não se mostra como uma casa mas um pequeno "museu" com uma sala onde data acontecimentos da sua vida e de Portugal, contamos também com uma sala de estudo com obras do poeta, com exposições temporárias e uma exposição de um fotógrafo conceituado setubalense que vale a pena conhecer. Aconselho a visita pois é sempre importante e enriquecedor conhecer um pouco da história de Portugal, e qual a melhor forma senão através daqueles que a contaram.
reviews/6/text: Situada en la calle Edmond Bartissol, 12, en la zona alta de Setúbal, muy cerca de la iglesia de San Sebastián, se encuentra la casa donde nació el 15 de septiembre de 1765 el escritor Manuel María Barbosa du Bocage, máximo exponente de la poesía local. En 1864, gracias a una suscripción popular, se colocó en la fachada una lápida en su memoria. En 1888 la casa fue comprada por el vizconde Edmond Bartissol, que la donó al pueblo de Setúbal. En la actualidad alberga una biblioteca relacionada con la vida y obra del poeta, así como una galería para exposiciones temporales. Asimismo, se ubica en ella el Archivo Municipal de Fotografía Américo Ribeiro. La casa puede ser visitada de martes a viernes, de 09.00 a 12.30 y de 14.00 a 17.30 horas, y los sábados, de 14.00 a 18.00 horas. El precio de la entrada es 1,50 €. No es una visita ni mucho menos imprescindible, pero si contamos con tiempo no es mala idea acercarse a ella para conocer un poco más a fondo la figura de uno de los personajes más ilustres que ha dado la ciudad.
reviews/7/text: A Casa de Bocage é  pequena, bem como a sua exposição, mas vale a pena como homenagem ao poeta. Têm também uma exposição de fotografia muito interessante do Fotografo Américo, que deixou uma vasta coleção de fotografias.
reviews/8/text: Património a proteger, a obra, o pensamento, e a atitude de revolta renascentista de Bocage. Se foi um "Bon vivant", foi também um poeta, deixou obra prima da literatura além de ter sido um Don Juan nosso.

reviews/9/text: A Casa de Bocage é relativamente pequena, bem como a sua exposição, mas vale a pena como homenagem e introdução ao poeta. Alberga também uma exposição de fotografia muito interessante.

reviews/8/text:
A Igreja de Nossa Senhora da Anunciada é uma das igrejas com mais história da cidade.
Reza a lenda que, naquele local, vivia uma senhora muito pobre, que costumava acender uma fogueira à noite para se aquecer. Certo dia, colocou um tronco na fogueira, mas ele saltou para fora. Voltou a pegar nele e a atirá-lo ao fogo, mas ele voltou a saltar para fora. Até que a senhora decidiu olhar bem o tronco e perceber que este continua a imagem gravada de Nossa Senhora.

reviews/3/text: la playa de Anicha es una pequeña cala que se encuentra en el extremo izquierdo de la bonita playa de Creiro. Solo es accesible con marea baja, pudiendo llegar andando desde esta última y pasando antes por la cala de Monte Branco. Si le echamos bastante arrojo y continuamos, llegaremos a la playa dos Coelhos, lo que puede llegar a ser peligroso. Es una cala pequeña, de arena blanca, con mucha roca, aunque hay suficiente espacio para poder bañarnos sin peligro. El agua, como en toda la zona, muy fria, entre 18 y 20º los días que estuvimos nosotros. Es una calita muy pintoresca a la que vale la pena acercarse si estamos en la playa de Creiro. Evidentemente, venir expresamente a esta cala no merece la más mínima pena. Si venimos temprano, podremos dejar el coche en los aparcamientos que hay en la carretera o cerca del yacimiento arqueológico, muy cercano a la playa, vigilados y a un precio de 3 € el día completo. En caso contrario, nos tocará aparcar en el arcen de la carretera. La vuelta a Setúbal habrá que hacerla rodeando la sierra de Arrabida, ya que el tramo entre Figueirinha y Creiro solo se puede utilizar en un sentido desde las 9 de la mañana hasta las 8 de la tarde.
reviews/3/title: Bonita cala, pequeña e inaccesible con marea alta
reviews/4/text: Mesmo ao lado da praia do Creiro, temos a praia da anicha, onde antes tínhamos o grande monte branco de areia, formado através de uma enorme tempestade. Com correntes significativas a pouco metros.

reviews/8/text: Onde a natureza deslumbra e encanta. O pior desta praia será mesmo o estacionamento pelo que convém ir muito cedo.
reviews/9/text: A praia é uma joia incrustada na Serra da Arrábida. As água é cristalina e o mar se assemelha a uma piscina, sendo perfeito para as crianças. Também há a vantagem de se localizar em uma reserva, longe da barulheira e poluição das praias citadinas. Há bons restaurantes (apesar do preço ser um pouco alto). A desvantagem é a exiguidade de parqueamento e a temperatura da água (o que não chega a ser um impeditivo para o banho, principalmente para as crianças).  Dista aproximadamente 1 h de Lisboa.

reviews/0/text: O Chafariz é bonito está situado numa pequena praça,que sem ser o chafariz é normal e até passa despercebida,mas é bonita.Recomendo.Lembre-se não polua o ambiente,evite e recicle o plástico.Não abandone seu animal de estimação.
reviews/1/text: Um chafariz histórico da cidade e bem junto à avenida Luisa Todi, mas que se encontra recuado numa praça algo fria e impessoal. Merecia mais ...
reviews/2/text: Una bella fontana barocca che, come si legge nell’iscrizione sul retro, è stata realizzata a fine del Seicento. Forniva acqua proveniente dall’acquedotto degli Archi nella attuale Praça de Bocage, poi è stata spostata e ora ha solo uno scopo estetico.
reviews/3/text: Fue ordenada construir por el Senado del Ayuntamiento de la Villa de Setúbal en 1697, con el objetivo de integrarla en el plan para abastecer de agua a la ciudad. En 1937 fue trasladada de su primitiva ubicación, la antigua plaza de Sapal, actual plaza de Bocage, a la actual, la Plaza Teófilo Braga, en la concurrida Avenida Luisa Todi. Está construida en mármol blanco y rosa y compuesta por tres cuerpos principales; el primero de ellos es el depósito, donde cae el agua a través de las bocas de cinco mascarones esculpidos en bajorrelieve. En el cuerpo superior encontramos un templete rodeado por tres esferas. La fuente se remata por el escudo portugués coronado, sostenido por dos putti. Debido a la monumentalidad de la obra y a su ubicación tan céntrica, no debemos dejar de visitarla.
reviews/4/text: No centro de Setúbal numa praça simples mas com história, surge este monumento... em pedra e cheio de significado. É muito rápido e vale a pena o curto desvio desde a avenida Luíza Todi
reviews/5/text: Na praça encontra-se este chafariz, com umas características bastante interessante, que anteriormente se encontrava mesmo em frente a câmara na praça do Bocage. É um chafariz de dimensões medias. Acaba-se por se perder um pouco na praça pois a mesma não tem muito movimento e acaba por passar despercebido.
reviews/6/text: Monumento histórico de Setúbal. De notar os pormenores e o trabalho artístico referentes à época da sua construção. Monumento bonito para se visitar.
reviews/7/text:
vale a pena ver e tirar fotografias, está envolvido por um pequeníssimo jardim, mas é agradável, espero que quando o visitem esteja limpo...
Para qualquer lado estão no centro da cidade com as suas ruas estreitas e bem perto dos restaurantes de peixe assado. Se forem turistas com um cariz social à Cáritas diocesana de Setúbal fica logo por atrás, bem como a livraria na Casa Diocesana para quem quiser puder adquirir livros ou emblemática de cariz católico.
reviews/7/title: Um monumento de eleição da história de Setúbal
reviews/9/text: Fica na Baixa de Setúbal. Local muito frequentado pelos Setubalenses. Rodeado de pequeno comercio local, junto à Avenida Luisa Tody aonde se encontram muitos restaurantes de peixe assado, também fica perto do famoso mercado de Setúbal.
reviews/10/text: Pouca gente pára para ver o nosso património. Esta fonte, que já não serve como tal, teve os seus tempos áureos e neste momento serve para alegrar a vista dos curiosos que tentam descobrir na sua traça os pormenores do escultor. Vale a pena ver os pormenores.
reviews/11/text:
Situado no centro histórico de Setúbal, o Chafariz do Sapal, de 1697, é uma obra arquitectónica lindíssima implantada numa praça de calçada portuguesa.
Monumento bem cuidado e bem iluminado que permite tirar umas bonitas fotos à noite.
Existe um edifício antigo, decorado com um excelente graffiti em azul e branco, situado na esquina desta praça com a Avenida Luísa Todi.

ranking: #44 of 81 things to do in Setubal

reviews/0/text: The Setúbal pillory, lonely but majestic stone column, represented power, as well was a symbol of municipal authority and autonomy. It was the local for announcements and proclamations and it was also used to expose criminals
reviews/1/text: Localizado muito perto da avenida Luisa Todi,na Praça Marquês de Pombal ,podemos apreciar este excelente pelourinho,constrído no reinado de D.Maria.
reviews/2/text: Trata-se de um monumento que se encontra em excelente estado de conservação, inserido num espaço agradável, mas que passa quase despercebido pois o local é apenas de passagem, apesar de espaço possuir locais onde se pode descansar um pouco.
reviews/2/title: NÃO DEIXA DE SER UM MONUMENTO MAS PASSA QUASE DESPERCEBIDO
reviews/3/text: O Pelourinho de Setúbal está localizado na Praça Marquês de Pombal, possuí uma coluna de mármore branco, um capitel e inscrições em quatro faces que datam de 1774.
reviews/3/title: "Este pelourinho se mudou da praça ribeira[3] para esta real no ano de 1774"
reviews/4/text: O Pelourinho de Setúbal foi construído no reinado de D. Maria I e a sua localização era, originalmente, no Largo da Ribeira Velha. Era uma das representações do poder do Duque de Aveiro que detinha os direitos sobre a cidade. A coluna é de mármore e no topo o capitel é coríntio. O pedestal tem inscrições que contextualizam historicamente o monumento.
reviews/5/text: Local de grande importância histórica que remonta à instituição do foral da cidade de Setúbal. Atualmente, está situado numa praça na lateral da Avenida Luisa Todi e sem grande enquadramento.
reviews/6/text: Anche a Setubal si trova una gogna sotto forma di un pilastro. In questo caso è settecentesco e non molto decorato, essendo solo una colonna con capitello corinzio e iscrizioni alla base.
reviews/7/text: Local limpo, bem organizado e representativo da cultura portuguesa. Tem lugar para sentar e curtir o excelente café português.
reviews/8/text: El pelourinho, o picota, es una columna de piedra situada en un lugar destacado de una población, donde eran ejecutados o sometidos a escarnio los condenados por diversos delitos, principalmente durante los siglos XVI y XVII, sirviendo también como símbolo de la justicia y del poder. El pelourinho de Setúbal, situado en la plaza del Marqués de Pombal, consta de una columna corintia de mármol blanco veteado, procedente de la excavaciones efectuadas en Troia. El plinto se corona con una pirámide cuadrangular. Presenta un espigón de hierro, de cuya parte inferior penden piezas metálicas que simulan esferas golpeadas. Las inscripciones que presenta en sus cuatro lados cuentan la historia de la construcción de este símbolo, terminado en 1774, y que sustituyó a la antigua picota situada en la plaza de Ribeira Velha. Es un elemento presente en muchas poblaciones portuguesas y merece que nos detengamos un momento a contemplarlo.
reviews/8/title: Una de las muchas picotas que hay en el país
reviews/9/text: Ns praça marques de pombal encontra-se o não tão famoso pelourinho de Setubal. O espaço não e muito trabalhado nem valorizado. Até parece que esta um pouco ao abandono, a própria praça necessita de uma grande renovação para lhe dar um novo ar. O pelourinho perde-se um pouco, apesar se ser um grande elemento de destaque.
reviews/10/text: Não é um local de culto ou de visita obrigatoria, no entanto faz parte da história da cidade. Encontra-se no centro da cidade
reviews/12/text: Pelourinho de Setúbal, fica na baixa de Setúbal. Muito frequentado pelos Setubalenses, fica perto do famoso Bairro  de Troino - bairro piscatório aonde pode encontrar muitos restaurantes de peixe assado.

ranking_subcategory: #53 of 81 things to do in Setubal
reviews/0/text: Este auditório está localizado bem no centro de Setúbal,e com espaço para serem feitos espectáculos.A pintura num dos lados do auditório é extraordinária.
reviews/1/text: Quando Sérgio Odeith foi convidado a pintar este mural em Setúbal, perguntaram-lhe se poderia ser algo relacionado à cidade. Odeith fez uma pesquisa e escolheu uma foto de 1933 de um fotógrafo de Setúbal chamado Américo Augusto Ribeiro. Um dia, foi procurado por um homem que lhe disse que o menino do mural era o tio dele e que, agora com mais de 90 anos, ainda era vivo. Mais tarde, o menino da foto, foi levado por sua filha para ver a pintura. Foi nesse momento que ele chamou a atenção para uma atadura que ele tinha na perna esquerda resultado de uma ferida. A arte recriando a vida.

name: Fonte de Palhais
ranking: #50 of 81 things to do in Setubal
ranking_subcategory: #50 of 81 things to do in Setubal
reviews/0/text: We found this fountain on the way back to railway station, nice piece of history and well worth a visit.
reviews/1/text:
A Fonte de Palhais, também conhecida como chafariz da praça ou chafariz de S. Bernardo, situa-se junto a um antigo convento de freiras Bernardas. Esta obra pombalina em mármore branco pode ser visitada em plena avenida 5 de outubro com a rua de santa maria  e encontra-se envolvida por um arranjo ajardinado que a separa da via pública.Em 1772, o Marquês de Pombal terá dado ordem à Câmara de Setúbal para pagar a despesa respeitante à construção do chafariz e respetiva canalização. O diretor da obra foi o coronel de engenharia José Bruno de Cabedo, mas desconhece-se o grande mestre do cinzel responsável pelas bicas em forma de
expressivas carrancas presentes no conjunto. Destaque ainda para a decoração: arabescos, o escudo de armas de Portugal, flores, troncos, folhas, bagas de loureiro, tudo encimado por uma coroa  com cruz de alto-relevo.

ranking: #68 of 81 things to do in Setubal

reviews/0/text: Igreja de construção do séc.17,A imagem do Senhor do Bonfim era das mais veneradas em todo o país na centúria de setecentos. O próprio rei D. João V, em 1711, visitou Setúbal, cumprindo uma promessa que fez quando o seu pai esteve doente, a essa Imagem. Vinham muitos devotos à capela, instalando-se nas hospedarias contíguas. Era importante como início ou terminus de procissões, sendo também aí que terminava a Via Sacra. Na capela, são de salientar os azulejos setecentistas, uma imagem denominada Nossa Senhora dos Homens e pintura da mesma época bem como a talha dourada barroca. Após o terramoto de 1755, a reconstrução parcial da nave afectou a parte superior dos painéis de azulejo. Este santuário está na origem do muito famoso Senhor do Bonfim na Cidade de Salvador (Baía), no Brasil.

description: Discover The Nature is your company in Lisbon to show you the coolest places such as SINTRA and ARRABIDA. Come and discover the best places by 4x4 or in our Kayaks. We can show you the highest places in a very cool hike. Or if you prefer to see the depths we can take you in a caving experience. But if all you want is adrenaline we have the perfect activity for you, Coasteering! Contact us!
name: Discover The Nature - Outdoor Events
offer_group/offer_list/0/title: Soft Coasteering - Arrábida Port
offer_group/offer_list/1/title: Arrabida Adventure Circuit
ranking: #1 of 35 Boat Tours & Water Sports in Setubal
ranking_subcategory: #1 of 35 Boat Tours & Water Sports in Setubal
reviews/0/text: Steep, challenging, exciting and quite spectacular! We felt very safe, both with equipment, guide (Marco) and guidance and had a great day climbing. Even though the Via Ferrata is not long, it was well worth the drive and the day. Highly recommended!
reviews/0/title: Spectacular experience - Via Ferrata Santa Luzia
reviews/1/text: Perfectly arranged Abseiling experience by the team (Marco and Rafaelo). Picked us up on time and took lots of pictures throughout. They were very helpful and clear with their instructions and made the whole day very fun. I would most definitely recommend.
reviews/2/text:
Marco, What a great guy, couldn’t have been more helpful and reassuring.
I’ve been coasteering before in Cornwall, where the swell comes into play more, but this was just as much fun. Some of the limestone caves are magical. 
I would definitely recommend this.
reviews/3/text: We went as a group of about 10 friends, an easy day trip from Lisbon. Marco and Pedro are such friendly, humorous guys! They had patience with everyone in the group, taking time to encourage and allowing us all to push our limits a bit while keeping us very safe.  They had everything we needed in terms of equipment and were well-organized. The tour offered opportunities to jump, rappel, zip line, and swim. Very active and you definitely need to be fit in order to enjoy.  I highly recommend a coasteering trip with these guys and hope to do it again!
reviews/3/title: Fantastic coasteering day with Marco and Pedro!
reviews/4/text: Perfect adventure for everyone who likes nature. If you like some adrenalin you can jump from cliffs of 12 metres, do slide and rappel. Of course you can still enjoy the experience if you don't want to jump and this type of stuff because you'll visit beautiful caves and beaches and get to swim in the beautiful water of Arrábida.
reviews/5/text:
Great Team, always concern with the security and well being of the clients. Outstanding spirit. I highly recommend Discover, instructors ten stars :)

Thank You for the stunning Day.

Wishing you all the Best.

Célia Costa
reviews/6/text:
The 3 partners in the business Marco, Nuno and Pedro are super cool friendly funny and well organised.

Great day coasteering with Marco. The equipment and attention to safety made the day Adrenalin fuelled fun!

They offer return pick up which Nuno drove.

There is a great cafe to have lunch in after the excursion so do not worry about taking food.

Marco took time to take lots if pictures which they do not charge for wanting it to be part of the experience and memories.

Top top top guys, company and experience. They do other adventures which I would definitely use them for if I return to Lisbon, the drive to the National Park was only around 30 minutes.
reviews/6/title: Fantastic experience cannot rate these guys and coasteering trip highly enough
reviews/7/text: Great experience coasteering, staff were all very friendly and all equipment provided.  The views were beautiful the activities were varied from jumps to a bit of rock climbing and abseiling + exploring caves.  Would recommend this experience to anybody it was truly memorable.  Thanks to all the staff for a great day
reviews/8/text:
Spent 4 hours coaststeering in the most beautiful surroundings.  Jumping off cliffs, climbing cliff faces, exploring caves, abseiling and even a death slide at the end! 

The team were superb, looked after us well and kept us safe. Real value for money, I would highly recommend this company.
reviews/9/text:
First time "coasteering" but the whole experience was awesome.
Everyone on the staff was really friendly and helpful, always looking out for our safety. 
I can recommend it to anyone! :)
reviews/10/text: Great tour with Pedro, must be the best driver in Lisbon! Highly reccomend it. The off-road tour was fantastic
reviews/11/text:
Met 10 vrienden hebben wij afgelopen week de Caving experience gedaan in het Arrabida natuurgebied. De tocht begon met een 10 min hike naar de ingang van de grot. Daar aangekomen werden wij door twee instructeurs begeleid door de grotten van Portugal. 

De nauwe ruimtes en het klimmen in een donkere grot zorgt voor gezonde spanning en veel avontuur. Bij sommige nauwe doorgangen is het even passen en meten waardoor je soms buiten je comfort zone moet stappen en door moet zetten. Uiteindelijk kom je uit op z'n 22 meter onder de grond, op het laagste punt. Na 3,5 uur (afhankelijk van de snelheid van je groep) stonden wij weer buiten, met een grote dosis adrenaline, spanning en ook voldoending dat iedereen het gehaald heeft. 

De instructeurs zijn vriendelijk en helpen iedereen om door de smalle gang te manoeuvreren. Daarnaast bieden ze ook een transfer aan vanuit Lisabon naar Arribida voor €25,- per persoon. 

Marco, bedankt voor alle goede zorgen en de spannende beleving in de grotten! Deze ervaring zullen wij niet snel vergeten.

Mitchel
reviews/11/title: Spannend en gewaagde Caving experience in Arrabida.
reviews/12/text: Tivemos uma divertida experiência de Rappel na Arrábida, foram muito simpáticos e disponíveis e fizémos 3 descidas  Obrigada ao João e especialmente ao Marco também pela assistência após a actividade. Silvia e Rui
reviews/13/text: Um grande dia de vias Ferratas em Sta. Luzia e na S. das Talhadas, o Marco é um excelente guia que nos providenciou material tecnico e garantiu todas as condições de segurança, além dos conselhos de quem tem grande experiência neste tipo de actividades
reviews/14/text: Tive um dos melhores dias de sempre, a explorar Vias Ferratas. Recomendo a todos os que gostam de uma experiência diferente e desafiante. E com o Marco ficamos em excelentes mãos.
reviews/15/text:
Já fiz algumas experiencias com a Discover The Nature, e têm sido sempre brutais!!
Ainda tenho mais algumas para fazer em breve.
Seguramente para repetir.
reviews/16/text:
Excelentes profissionais, bons equipamentos, atividades muito bem organizadas e o melhor de tudo permite-nos conhecer locais extraordinários!!
Recomendo!!!
reviews/17/text:
Tudo bem organizado desde o início e sempre com uma bela comunicação entre ambas as partes. Fomos com um grupo de 20 jovens fazer um passeio pedestre pela arrábida, sempre com muitas explicações dos vários pontos de paragem e de passagem, pelo Marco o monitor, ambos os monitores foram espetaculares.
Já temos outro dia para a próxima semana marcado e queremos experimentar todas as atividades disponíveis no futuro...
reviews/18/text:
Tenho feito várias atividades nacional e internacionalmente como arborismo, skydiving, snorkelling, snowboard, etc... E de longe o Circuito Aventura (escalada, rapel e espeleologia) da Discover the Nature foi das melhores experiências que já fiz! Desde as paisagens e emoções até ao profissionalismo da equipa. Foi uma experiência fantástica do início ao fim. 
Recomendo a Discover the Nature tanto como animador turístico tanto como parceiro!
reviews/18/title: Das melhores experiências que já fiz!
reviews/19/text:
Um passeio espetacular com muito boas vistas e no meio da natureza.
Sem dúvida para repetir.
Obrigado aos guias e organizadores.

reviews/0/text: Good material and very chill teachers - we were 6 and we all enjoyed it very much - Arrabida is amazing we recommend!
reviews/1/text: This tour was not what I had planned, but it turned out to be the best thing.  I had some company out on the water instead of going out on my own.  Natasha was able to take me further around the coast as she knew the waters and pointed out all the landmarks.  She helped me with my technique when I felt unstable.  And made the experience so much fun. She also took photos of me whilst I was out there, which I wouldn't have been able to do just renting a board myself.  I totally recommend it!!
reviews/2/text:
Far better experience than I was expecting, mostly because of Tiago Estanislau (the instructor).
Looking forward to do it again.
reviews/3/text: Had a really nice time! Thanks for this amazing experience, for all the pictures we asked for and specially for the all the time and help you provided. We'll surely repeat!
reviews/4/text: Excellent support and experience! Friendly and professional staff. The location is incredibly beautiful!
reviews/5/text: Experiência altamente para quem nunca tinha feito esta atividade. Recomendo o passeio com amigos, muito giro e divertido! Instrutores impecáveis e muito atenciosos! Sem dúvida para repetir! Um beijinno ao Tiago e à Natacha
reviews/6/text: Una magnífica opción para disfrutar de Portinho de Arrabida. El monitor insistió en las normas de seguridad y además nos dio buenos consejos para disfrutar de la zona.
reviews/7/text: Foi uma experiência excelente. Profissionalismo, simpatia e diversão. Fomos com os nossos filhos e para além de ter sido uma experiência muito divertida e inesquecível, os monitores foram super cuidadosos com os nossos filhotes. Recomendo e é, seguramente, uma experiência a repetir. Adorámos! :)
reviews/8/text:
Excelentes profissionais! Muito obrigada pela paciência! Gostei imenso da experiência!
A repetir num dia com mais sol!
reviews/9/text:
Professores Excelentes!!! Incansáveis , dedicados! 
Experiência recomendada!! 5*
Momento sublime! 
A repetir!!
reviews/10/text: Foi realmente uma actividade bem organizada para um grupo de amigos que se juntou para passar uma manhã muito agradável. Ambiente único em plena harmonia com a natureza. A repetir!
reviews/11/text: Una grata experiencia. Natasha es muy buena monitora. El sitio es espectacularmente bonito y las condiciones del mar al menos el día que nosotros fuimos, eran óptimas. Una experiencia para repetir
reviews/12/text: Belíssima experiência! Muita simpatia e disponibilidade sem descurar a segurança e o bem-estar de cada um dos elementos do grupo! Obrigada, Tiago e Natacha! Paisagem imperdível! Recomendo vivamente!!!
reviews/13/text: Stand Up Paddle num local paradisíaco! Os instrutores foram extremamente disponíveis, atenciosos e simpáticos, quer no que respeita à marcação e agendamento quer durante e após a experiência. Bom material, boa disposição e segurança garantidos. Fotografias incluídas ;-)  Obrigada Tiago e Natacha! Até breve
reviews/14/text:
Maravillosa experiencia, natasha nos explicó muy bien las normas para hacer el SUP de  antes de entrar al agua y durante la experiencia siempre iba muy atenta de que pusieramos en práctica sus consejos. Es muy simpática ya agradable, incluso nos hizo unas fotos muy chulas durante la experiencia.
No pongo el 5 porque empezamos bastante más tarde de lo que habíamos concertado, pero por lo demás excelente todo! para repetir :)
reviews/15/text:
Dia fantástico com pessoal profissional e simpático que sabem cativar e receber. 
Bom material e condições para todos os participantes na actividade e com grande foco na segurança .
reviews/16/text:
Uma manhã de domingo bem passada num ambiente descontraído, divertido e profissional. Os instrutures Natasha, Nadia, João e Tiago foram incríveis e proporcionaram-me uma experiência inesquecível incentivando os participantes a não desistir. O resultado é que chegamos todos em cima da prancha :-) e com um sorriso na esperança de voltarmos a repetir esta aventura muito brevemente.
Recomendo definitivamente a até um dia destes  ;-)
reviews/17/text: Foi a minha estreia a fazer Paddle Stand Up e não poderia ter escolhido melhor sitio e instrutores para me ensinarem a como fazer. Os intrutores eram todos muito simpáticos e atenciosos. Ao longo do percurso os instrutores registraram os melhores momentos com os seus telemoveis, para um dia mais tarde recordarmos. O equipamento utilizado estava em excelentes condicoes transmitindo grande segurança. O local em si é maravilhoso. Ficou uma vontade enorme de voltar de repetir. Recomendo a todos esta experiência :)
reviews/17/title: Manhã maravilhosa a fazer Paddle Stand Up
reviews/18/text: Simpatia, profissionalismo e onde a segurança dos participantes está acima de tudo para usufruir de um dia espetacular, já fiz este tour com um grupo de amigos, com o marido e num convívio empresarial, todos eles recomendados e cada um com a sua magia!
reviews/19/text: Foi brutal. Recomendo sem dúvida... o Tiago foi o nosso instrutor e foi mesmo 5* inclusive deu nos muitas dicas para visitar a cidade. Ainda tivemos direito a fotografias.. Vamos voltar

name: Dolphin Bay PT
ranking: #2 of 48 Tours in Setubal
ranking_subcategory: #2 of 48 Tours in Setubal
reviews/0/text: Great team with very good boat with great conditions and they make sure that you finish the tour after watching the incredible beings Dolphins are. Respect for nature. Loved it and highly recomend it.
reviews/1/text:
It was my birthday and I wanted to do something special. Nature has always been a part of my life, growing up in South Africa, I always enjoyed the wonders of the animal life. 
Deciding on a boat ride and to see the Dolphin life  was such an experience. Not only is it so romantic for couples but a fun outing for family and truly educational for kids. 
To see a school of dolphins swimming meters away from you is such an experience. 
Exploring and learning about the coastal area of Arrabida was just magical.  Not only do I recommend this, but I highly recommend it. The crew are really friendly and ate fluent in both Portuguese and English.
reviews/2/text: I participated as a solo traveler in September 2022. The tour was great, I enjoyed it a lot and I would like to thank you the dedicated team for this special experience :-) I really appreciate how the biologists care about the environment and wellbeing of the  Dolphins and also educate tourists in this regard, I think it's really important :-). Tour was really worth it.
reviews/3/text: It was all amazona. The crew, the boat and the food. I absolutly recomend, the experience we had a great sunset.
reviews/4/text:
The crew on this trip is headed by marine biologists who have names for the dolphins that live in the bay.   How great is that?  Those dolphins are an essential part of the identity of Setúbal.  In addition to these very special dolphins that spend their whole lives in Setúbal (an excellent choice), we went out far enough to see some that roam the coast.  

Even if there weren't dolphins the boat ride alone would be worth the price of admission.  The coast is amazing and there are parts you just wouldn't see without being on a boat. 

Get there a bit early.  Most folks are coming from a distance and line up to get their choice of seats.  We got there a bit later, but got lucky.  Next time, we'll get there 30 minutes before time rather than 10 and not leave it to chance.
reviews/4/title: Go see the dolphins.  It's a great couple of hours.
reviews/5/text: Excellent trip. Staff was very well prepared and friendly, boat was comfortable and clean. We saw many dolphins and the staff recognized them one by one , they even knew the names of the dolphins! Strongly recommended!
reviews/6/text:
Great crew and great service. They warn you upfront that there is a chance you will not see dolphins. If that is the case you get a voucher for another day. 

During the trip you get a lot of explanations about the dolphins that live in the bay. 

Recommended
reviews/7/text: Nice clean boat, very friendly crew, a lot of information during the trip and we didn’t stop sailing until we saw the dolphins. Crew is very respectful to the animals.
reviews/8/text:
An amazing experience.
The staff is awesome and has biologists that explain a lot of facts related to the dolphins and their habitat.
The boat is comfortable and safe.
The bay behind Serra da Arrábida  is gorgeous.
reviews/8/title: A must go! It is awesome!
reviews/9/text: The trip with the Dolphin Bay was a fantastic experience. Everything that was promised was delivered. We saw dolphins and the sunset was beautiful. The staff on board was very friendly and responded immediately to all our questions. This is definitely worth repeating. Highly recommended for anyone visiting Setubal and wanting to see the Arrabida in a different light.
reviews/10/text: Everything went perfectly, very clean and safe boat, great staff. I recommend to anyone who wishes to see dolphin in Portugal.
reviews/11/text: Relaxing and educational cruise to see and learn about the dolphins in Baía do Sado. Commentary in several languages, expertly delivered by a marine biologist. Nice boat with restrooms and small cafe.
reviews/12/text: Professional godd boat! We saw the Dolphins. Sun day beautifull landscape a great birthday!! Recommended 100%
reviews/13/text: Amazing Dolphin trip with a great group of marine biologists! Best place ever !!! Setubal and Arrábida is beautiful with amazing views !
reviews/14/text:
The Crew was very nice! My boyfriend got seasick, but they took great care of us. We saw a lot of dolphins quite close up and the marine biologist was very patient with all our questions. Great experience, really worth it would definitely recommend. There was a school class with little kids on board with us, but they were on a different deck for most of the time and really lovely. 
After the tour we visited the Casa da Baía just across from the harbour, it was free and great to get some more information about dolphins in general and the specific population in the bay.
reviews/15/text:
Best dolphin watching ever!
Very professional crew taking into account that we are visiting the home of these mammals. They use only electric motor when around the dolphins and The animals seemed happy and playful around us.
A lot of information was given about each individual dolphin - their nature, habbits, family etc. 
Don’t miss this one!
reviews/16/text: Spacious and clean boat, friendly and knowledgeable crew that´s familiar with the local dolphin population.
reviews/17/text:
Such a perfect afternoon! 
Everything was better than expected:
- nothing commercial
- pure passion (the crew and the dolphins seam to really like and appreciate each other!)
- nature at its best with people that are passionate about it
reviews/17/title: We are looking forward to meet the dolphins ant their friends from the dolphin bay next year! Thank you again!
reviews/18/text: Beautiful experience! Started on time, very helpfull and knowledgeable staff, the boat was very clean and spacious. The best part was the dolphins, watching them laying on the nets above the water was amazing!!
reviews/19/text:
We had the best time on the tour. Firstly the boat was
clean, modern and spacious. We had a fantastic spot on the upper deck to take in the view. The dolphin viewing was absolutely incredible. We really appreciated the time the marine biologists took to tell us all about the dolphins that live there. They have a real love and respect for them and it shows in the non intrusive way they interact with them. The little stop by the shore for us to have a swim was an absolute blast, just wish it could have been longer! 

Fantastic tour, that I will certainly do again!

reviews/0/text: If you are looking for adventure or just a weekend off to clean your mind and refill your batteries do not hesitate and spend a time in a place where  you will have the feeling that time is stopped.
reviews/1/text:
This day trip was just unforgettable.
We started by going on a beautiful trail inside nature and we learnt how to climb medium level natural walls, amazing!!
Then we went to a local restaurant and had a fantastic complete meal, to gain some energy for the long walk and montain climb ahead. 
We climbed the highest point of Serra da Arrábida and it was amazing to get up there and see the beautiful 360º view over city and sea.
Samuel was a terrific guide and monitor, always nice and helpful with everything. 
We sure want to repeat the experience in other places with Trilhos e cumes.
Thank you!!
reviews/2/text: What the great trip Trilhos e Cumes offered to us!!!!! The guides are very nice, Passos was great too arranging everything for us. It's the great life experience to be there. Highly recommending Trilhos e Cumes.
reviews/3/text: Foram 2 dias excelentes, tudo feito com calma e bem organizado. O Samuel tem muita experiência e sabe transmiti-la. Aconselho!
reviews/4/text: Este curso foi feito na Serra da Estrela, o que por si só, penso ser o melhor local em Portugal para a prática do mesmo. Fomos rececionados pelo nosso monitor Samuel Passos que nos informou de todos os pormenores e desenvolvimentos do curso. A estadia apresentou-se satisfatória bem como a alimentação. No que respeita ao curso foram dadas, compreendidas e cumpridas as aulas teóricas bem como as aulas práticas, com um grande profissionalismo por parte do nosso monitor. Deixo completamente em aberto novos cursos pela empresa Trilhos e Cumes. Um bem hajam.
reviews/5/text:
dois fins-de-semana muito bem passados. excelente profissional disposto a partilhar o seu conhecimento e experiência em Montanhismo.
Grande abraço ao durão Samuel Passos
reviews/6/text: Fui muito bem recebido e não tenho nada a apontar no tratamento que me foi dado. Toda a experiência correspondeu às minhas expectativas e fiquei com vontade de participar em outros eventos da Trilhos e Cumes. Só tenho a dizer bem.
reviews/7/text:
Excelente fim de semana, onde a cereja no topo do bolo, foi sem duvida os momentos que partilhamos com o Samuel...uma pessoa que nos cativou logo desde o inicio.
Aconselho vivamente os seus serviços.
Bem hajam Samuel por tudo
reviews/8/text: Fiz no passado mês de Novembro o curso de montanhismo. O Samuel é super competente, garante que todos aprendem e mantém a motivação da equipa. Recebeu-nos super bem no seu Chalé e recomendo vivamente que façam cursos com ele!
reviews/9/text: Curso muito bem estruturado, boa parte teórica antes da abordagem ao terreno. Monitor muito bom com muita experiência. Tudo muito bom.
reviews/10/text: Acolhimento 5*, paisagem fabulosa, decoração com conceitos e materiais da região.Possibilidade de juntar atividades na Serra, guiadas pelo anfitrião.O meu alojamento preferido nas Penhas da Saúde.A repetir, sem dúvida!
reviews/10/title: fim-de-semana 5/out no refúgio Trilhos e Cumes
reviews/11/text: na chegada à Serra da Estrela ,esperamos tempo austero e desconforto ,mas a Trilhos e Cumes faz tudo para essas sensações desaparecerem . O responsável Samuel Passos ,o Honorável Cidadão faz com todo o tempo tenha interesse .
reviews/12/text: Excelente, motivadora, muita adrenalina, espaço acolhedor, muita hospitalidade e boa disposição.Recomendo vivamente!
reviews/13/text: O curso de montanhismo foi fantástico e superou as minhas expectativas. O instrutor sempre de bom humor e disponível, com um plano de formação bem estruturado, demonstrou um profundo conhecimento teórico e prático da prática de montanhismo que aliada ao fascínio pelo desafio da montanha foram muito importantes para a minha aprendizagem nos 4 dias de curso e para concluir com sucesso as atividades. O alojamento no chalé foi também excelente. Uma verdadeira “casa de montanha” com todo o conforto e uma localização excecional integrada na paisagem natural da Serra, que permite momentos ótimos de evasão e contacto com a natureza.Em resumo aprendi muito e foi uma experiência que recomendo integralmente.
reviews/14/text: Participei no curso que superou todas as minhas expectativas. De enaltecer toda a capacidade do Samuel em  apresentar os conteúdos, que é alicerçada numa verdadeira paixão pela montanha e que é transmitida a todo o grupo - a verdadeira “cordada” ! O chalé, enquanto espaço, consegue transmitir perfeitamente a montanha - é o que se pretende !Excelente - voltarei certamente!G-9 Rocks
reviews/15/text: O instrutor é profissional, bem-disposto e sempre disponível para esclarecimento de dúvidas. Aprendi muito e recomendo vivamente. O local é propício a bons momentos e voltarei certamente.
reviews/16/text: Foi uma experiência excepcional com um acompanhamento 5 estrelas por parte do Samuel.Excelente acomodação no chalet. Não há palavras para descrever o tão fantástico foi... Apenas recomendo vivamente!
reviews/17/text: Foi a primeira vez que fizemos escalada na Natureza e gostámos muito da experiência. A paisagem na Serra da Arrábida é linda, e o Instrutor (Samuel) foi 5 estrelas!
reviews/18/text:
Excelente organização, bom domínio da matéria, boa localização.
Um curso de montanhismo, onde se aprendeu bastante e praticamos com boas condicoes e excelente dicas.
Foi muito bom.
reviews/18/title: Uma excelente organização, bom domínio da matéria, boa localização.
reviews/19/text:
Simpatia, profissionalismo, responsabilidade, diversão, aventura, descoberta...
Excelente formação para a prática de montanhismo.
reviews/19/title: Se não fez não sabe o que perde

description: A Arrabida Experiences é assim uma entidade gestora de destino, focada no aproveitando, em pleno, de todas as potencialidades do Parque Natural da Arrábida enquanto destino de excelência, associado ao turismo sustentável – partilhando e praticando práticas melhores e mais conscientes a fim de contagiar os demais e contribuir para a redução da pegada ecológica.
name: Arrabida Experiences
offer_group/offer_list/0/title: Try Scuba Diving in Arrabida Natural Park (Near Lisbon) with pictures
offer_group/offer_list/1/title: Kayaking and snorkeling in Arrábida with photos!
offer_group/offer_list/2/title: Open Water Diver Course in Arrabida Natural Park (Near Lisbon)
ranking: #3 of 48 Tours in Setubal
ranking_subcategory: #3 of 48 Tours in Setubal
reviews/0/text:
I've recently completed my Open Water Dive course and the overall experience was great! The gear supplied was good and in good condition.
The instructors were very friendly and helpful and they were very patient with anyone who was struggling to do any part of the course. We didn't manage to dive always according to plan because the tides didn't allow it and they mostly had a backup plan, which made me feel safe and reassured. While diving, even though the visibility wasn't great and that the main focus was to learn and improve our diving skills, the instructors also did their best to show us a few of the good things the sea has to offer.
The tea and cookies given after each dive were great! :D
reviews/1/text: I did my Open Water Dive course with them and what a great decision that was! The team was fantastic and made the whole experience more enjoyable. They really inspired us to continue with this journey of diving and they were so friendly that I hope this was not the only encounter with them. I hope to dive with them soon! I totally recommend you doing the course here if you are thinking about it, so you have the best experience possible with the safety and patience that it requires along with lots of fun and learning!
reviews/2/text:
Amazing experience, amazing spots to dive,  amazing wild life 
Very friendly and professional intructors and guides.. best vibe
reviews/3/text:
Great team, always helping the clients and divers. Allowing permanent evolution of divers .
Safety cames first and Arrábida experiences is a good exemple of best practices.
reviews/3/title: Friendship and permanent focus on clients
reviews/4/text: Took my sailor's license at Arrabida Experiences and  it was 5 stars, professionalism, simpathy and experience, I will pursue other experiences with this team for sure!
reviews/5/text: Filipe and Joao took us for our first diving experience and it was simply amazing. The team was really friendly and we didn't felt much on a touristic tour but simply out with friends. I was personally quite afraid of my first dive but they were extremely professional and I always felt safe and ended up just enjoying my dive without worries. Wonderful team and wonderful experience!
reviews/6/text: We did a great dive with Rudi, he is a great instructor, all very safe, the gear was amazing and the dive was super fun! Totally recommended :)
reviews/7/text: Somos unas chicas del sur de España (Huelva) y hemos terminado encantadas como el trato de los encargados de la actividad. Han estado muy atentos y ayudándonos en todo. Muy recomendable
reviews/8/text:
Fiz o Curso Open Water Diver, e não podia ter tido melhor experiência.
Uma equipa de simpatia extrema, super acessivel, atenciosa, com excelentes capacidades de comunicação, divertida e muito focada na aprendizagem e segurança dos alunos.
Utilização de material de qualidade, para mergulhos em segurança.
Obrigado a toda a equipa!
reviews/9/text: Fiz o curso de open water diver com a equipa da Arrábida Experiences e foi uma experiência espetacular! A equipa é fantástica, super prestável e boa onda. Ensinam com bastante rigor tudo o que é preciso para começar uma jornada a explorar o oceano. Estava com algum receio pois tenho alguma ansiedade com a profundidade mas a calma e profissionalismo dos instrutores fizeram com que essa ansiedade se tornasse em ótimos momentos e passeios incríveis debaixo de água. Se também pretendes fazer o curso ou mesmo outras atividades, esta é a equipa certa!
reviews/10/text: Equipa excelente! Super profissionais e com muito conhecimento. Recomendo! Os locais de mergulho são lindos.
reviews/11/text: Fiz o curso de Open Water Diver em Janeiro e foi uma ótima experiência, recomendo vivamente! Toda a equipa foi 5 estrelas desde o primeiro dia, super prestáveis e atenciosos. Ajudaram-me a lidar com os nervos de forma super profissional e estavam sempre preocupados com o nosso bem estar e em termos a melhor experiência possível. O curso permitiu desafiar-me e sair da minha zona de conforto. No final dos mergulhos tínhamos sempre um cházinho para ajudar a aquecer e bolachinhas. Vimos paisagens lindas e vários animais (peixes, ouriços do mar, santola, choco, polvo,...). Foi muito divertido, tenciono voltar a mergulhar com a Arrábida Experiences!
reviews/11/title: Curso de mergulho com a melhor equipa
reviews/12/text:
Fiz o curso Open Water Diver com o meu filho mais velho em Junho e foi excelente 
Desde então mergulho com a Arrábida Experiences regularmente
reviews/13/text: O mergulho, o profissionalismo e a integração com que a equipa nos recebe, aliados a  umas paisagens subaquáticas incríveis
reviews/14/text: A parte favorita é o belo chá com bolachinhas depois do mergulho! E claro toda a fantástica equipa
reviews/15/text: Ver o mundo subaquático só no Arrábida Experriences, excelente escola de mergulho. Venham fazer um batismo de mergulho
reviews/16/text: Muito bom! Equipa excecional e muito profissional. Senti-me seguro durante todo o mergulho e a experiência para além de incrível foi divertida!
reviews/17/text: Equipa muito profissional, atenciosa, disponível. Superou a minha expetativa. Adorei a experiência??
reviews/18/text:
Excelente experiencia en familia el tour en kayak por la costa de Arrabida. Nos encantó ver la costa desde el agua y visitar las grutas en la roca con una inesperada sorpresa final. Además pudimos hacer snorkel por cerca de la costa.
Nuestra monitora Inés encantadora. Nos explicó perfectamente las curiosidades de la zona y estuvo en todo momento súper pendiente de todos nosotros.
Lo recomiendo totalmente!!
reviews/18/title: Tour en kayak por costa Arrabida
reviews/19/text: Passeio de caiaque com a Inês foi ótimo, divertido ótima profissional. Ótimo guia turística , simpática nota 10

description: Its company that makes private tours at sea. along arrabida coast, troia and sado estuarium. Dolphing watching Rent boats Rent jetsky
name: SetubalAlive
ranking: #8 of 48 Tours in Setubal
ranking_subcategory: #8 of 48 Tours in Setubal
reviews/0/text: Had a great trip aboard the Cachondo - went to Arrábida coast, to the sandbank at Tróia, to the old Roman excavation site and even saw a school of dolphins. The boat was beautiful and comfortable, held plenty of drinks and was manned by a magnificent crew. Thank you so much - it was a great day and the perfect completion as well as the highlight of our vacation to Portugal.
reviews/0/title: The perfect daytrip at Setúbal / Tróia
reviews/1/text: Fantastic half day thanks to a wonderful crew and great food and wines! On the way back we saw dolphins which was the icing on the cake!
reviews/2/text: Although the weather was not great, and we started the day in the absolute mist, our skipper Ricardo took us to Troia where we visited an old Fishermen's village and received lots of insight information on the region.  Once the sun got out it was great to be able to see this part of Portugal from the sea.  We saw dophins and enjoyed a swim.  Tip: ask Ricardo for the address of his parents' restaurant, fresh grilled fish and his mum maskes great desserts!
reviews/3/text: Four hours on the water with Andre was excellent. Fantastic local knowledge and Andre shared the most beautiful spots with us. What a gorgeous day out and his love of the area made it very special. Thank you
reviews/4/text: Andre took our family of 14 out on Sunday 6th of October.  His passion and knowledge of the local area was fantastic and it was great to learn more about Setubal.  Andre clearly loves the area and is involved in the community in protecting this beautiful part of Portugal.  The restoration and running of his boat is a labour of love to him and we had a great couple of hours, relaxing, swimming and taking in the beautiful scenery.  We were lucky enough to see the dolphins on our way back to Troia and all in all a very memorable morning, thank you Andre.
reviews/5/text: We booked a 4 hours boat drive with Andre it was just amazing, Andre is from Setúbal speaks english, french, Spanish. We did a stop over where he offered us the local danish, with a nice glass of Muscat. I highly recommend him as he is a great person. Thanks to you and vanda.
reviews/6/text: If you take just one boat trip and you want someone with tremendous local knowledge, you cannot do better than André, who loves Setubal with all his heart. We took our three boys out on the water, to the biggest dolphins I have ever seen, and to hidden beaches available only by boat, and we could not have learned more from Wikipedia about the entire region. Andre is a gentleman and a great Portuguese fisherman who cares deeply about the future of Setubal. And after the trip, visit his family’s restaurant where his Mother is a master of desserts.
reviews/7/text: We had a fantastic day exploring the coast around Setubal with Vanda. We rented the San Remo for 8 hours, Vanda beeing the best skipper and guide we could ask for! The whole family (2 adults and 2 kids) loved it. Highly recommended!
reviews/8/text: Vanda took my wife and I out for a 4 hour tour around Tróia peninsula. It was excellent. Vanda gave us cool info about the area, took us dolphin watching, and even convinced us to take a dip in the “refreshingly cool” water. She even had a traditional drink and natas for us! Great time on the water.
reviews/9/text:
My husband and I spent a fabulous four hours on a small boat with Andre the owner of Setubal Alive.  We were able to go onto beaches and swim and went up and down the beautiful coast.
Andre is extremely knowledgeable about the area and knows this water and coast well. We felt in extremely good hands.
I can not think of a better way to see this area than from the water with Setubal Alive!
reviews/9/title: Fabulous day on the water with Andre!
reviews/10/text: It's my third trip aboard this amazing sailing boat and I simply can't get enough of it, every single time is different and surprising! The team is super friendly and welcoming, let's you personalize your trip and shows you what's best in the area, totally recommendable!! You won't regret it, totally worth it! Super fun for everyone, from sailing with dolphins to swimming close to hidden and paradisal beaches... like immersing yourself into an untouched area that few tourists know of...!
reviews/11/text: This is one of the best ways to see Setubal and the surrounding coast. My partner had seen a review of the boat tours and we were instantly intrigued. We decided to ring as with their only being the two of us we thought we'd see if it was possible to get a boat for just us. On the phone they were unbelievably helpful creating a bespoke trip to our specifications and budget. The trip itself did not disappoint. The beautiful scenery is enough to take your breath away, but friendly service, the chance to swim in the ocean a numerous times, dolphin watching and secluded beaches all made this an unforgettable day. This is a trip definitely worth making time for, don't hesitate.
reviews/12/text:
Wonderful late afternoon. You really get what you pay for and more...
Great crew, caring and accessible, young and entrepreneur. A few minuts from Lisbon, this adventure provides easy access to the most beautiful beach in Europe, the Galapinhos beach, where we dived. Road acess is almost impossible.
We watched a wonderful sunset, was offered a Moscatel Wine of the region, saw the family of Dolphins of the Sado river. Enjoyed seafood and contemplate the Arrabida and Troia Coast. Typical wine and music was something that was not lacking. Ideal for groups or large family. Certainly an experience to repeat.
reviews/13/text: Great experience! I will recommend my friends from England to go and have a great experience with Setubal Alive. You can enjoy  the mountain and visit very nice beaches. Prepare yourself to swim with the dolphins because they are always around. Thank you to Vanda and Julio for the experience!
reviews/14/text: When we got to the place the crew was already waiting with a big warm friendly smile, ready to introduce us to this place's uniqueness. We set sail from the Setúbal harbor at lunch time and admired a beautiful regatta with Tróia in the background (coincidentally). While we were discovering beautiful and hidden spots to dive, the crew explained the local history, its wildlife and fauna, the richness of Arrabida Natural Park. After a quick stop to dive (in crystal clear waters) we jumped into an empty sand island, full of sea life, colorful seashells and rocks, in the middle of the Sado river. An authentic tour, unique in its style, with the best company, a couple of explorers, eager to show the best this place has!! Greatly Recommended!!!
reviews/15/text: We had an absolute perfect day on board of Cachondo with the best crew ever. They did everything to let us feel welcome and fulfill every wish (even those, we did not utter aloud). We could admire the Arrabida Mountains from the waterside, visited lonely beaches at Troia, went for a swim there, had a perfect lunch on board and even could watch the dolphins which live in the Sado estuary. When the trip ended we did not want to leave the boat and could have stayed for ever.
reviews/15/title: The most perfect day of our stay in Setubal
reviews/16/text: Experiência em família magnifica! Equipa super simpática, prestável e que nos permitiu aproveitar em pleno este passeio inesquecível!  Recomendo a 100%.
reviews/17/text:
Fizemos um passeio de barco com 13 pessoas com a Setúbal Alive e só posso dizer bem da experiência. 
O barco está bem aproveitado em tremos de espaço. Tem almofadas à frente, em cima, poofs e paddle. A tripulação é 5 estrelas, muito prestável e  simpáticos, tentando tornar sempre o passeio o mais agradável possível.
Vimos golfinhos e paramos para dar mergulhos e andar de Paddle.
Recomendo claramente. Serviço top.
reviews/18/text:
Equipa super prestável, comunicação clara e bastante explicita.
Embarcações disponíveis em bom estado.
Parabéns à equipa e empresa
reviews/19/text:
Superbe expérience à Setubal.
Nous avons passé une journée complète en bateau avec notre skipper André francophone, enfant du pays qui a toutes les anecdotes pour comprendre le territoire.
A faire obligatoirement les paysages sont magnifiques, restaurant de plage à la clé

name: Vertigem Azul
photo/caption: watch the dolphins in this beautiful catamaran
ranking: #6 of 48 Tours in Setubal
ranking_subcategory: #6 of 48 Tours in Setubal
reviews/0/text: Nice boat tour, we liked it. The crew is friendly and the boat in good conditions. We have done it before and would do it again.
reviews/1/text: Very friend team, with a marine biologist on board to explain more about the native pod of dolphins. The team went above and beyond (and extended our trip by almost 2 hours) to ensure we saw what we came for. Also a bar on board!
reviews/2/text: It was a nice and pleasant trip, it can be cold, specially out in the sea so I would advise you take warm clothes. The crew has blankets if someone needs, but if you use one, it will limit your ability to move around the boat. Overall it was a great experience, one I hope to repeat someday!
reviews/3/text: Awful experience … the women in the booking office and on the phones are so unhelpful and rude. Ended up missing the boat with a 2 year old who was so sad to not have a chance to see the dolphins , due to poor communication and directions from the booking staff.   Do not use this business
reviews/4/text:
I received an email with the "Meeting Point" 10 min walk from where I was supposed to be. I wrote on instagram and to a fixed number (2652*****) that was identified and no answer. Only to a mobile contact ending in 907, where I was told it was not the right place and we had to arrive quickly and with the car parked far away from where we were supposed to be initially. 
We didn't see any dolphins or fish. And the introduction had to be requested by us to a member of staff who passed by where we were sitting, and it was only done in Spanish or French. 
We had a moment, for diving ... which lasted 10 minutes. 
Finally, they indicated that the expedition was from 9:30 to 12:30 ... we had an appointment at 3:00 p.m. at 100 km's of Setúbal. The expedition finished at 14:00. In the end we had no comment from the collaborators that we had not seen anything.
Conclusion, we did not see any dolphins, did not receive any final clarification from the team, badly indicated in the shared email, and it took an hour and a half longer than scheduled.
reviews/4/title: A disappointing experience. And very poorly organised.
reviews/5/text: We saw no dolphins at all which ok it can happen, but the company claim a 96% success rate. They should offer a partial refunds for the unlucky 4% or at least a free drink… dissapointed
reviews/6/text: A great experience watching dolphins and visiting the surrounding area by sea. The catamaran is very comfortable. The only negative is that less people should be allowed on the boat for each trip. Our boat had around 40 people on board
reviews/7/text: We had a wonderful experience seeing the dolphins - so nice to see mother and calf swimming together! It was a lovely day and our tour guides and crew were helpful and polite.
reviews/8/text: It was a good experience, the trip, the boat, and the dolphins' observation was perfect. However, as a local resident and Biologist, I was expecting to learn more about what's been done for dolphin conservation, about the history of this dolphin community, the importance of their habitat, maybe a little bit about Arrabida and its surroundings. There was only a very small interaction/explanation with the crew, a booklet was shown at a distance to show the dorsal fin ID of each dolphin and feeding habits. When stoping for a swim, the skipper was completely rude. Honestly, from a 25-year conservation company, I would expect much more.
reviews/9/text: Great crew and boat! Dolphins were beautiful! 10/10. English speaking crew. We were happy to join the tour.
reviews/10/text: Great service provided, include watching very nice doplhins group in open sea. The boat Jasmine is excellent boat for dolphin watching at open sea. Staff very friendly, helpfull and professional. The team provided detailed info about each member of dolphin group.
reviews/11/text: Fantastic. The trip was fantastic for children and adults. We really enjoyed it. We will recommend this vendor and this trip. We saw the dolphins, we enjoyed the sights.
reviews/12/text:
Everything was amazing ! Highly recommend . Great program for family’s and couples also ! 
The crew was very very nice and we had the best time !
reviews/13/text:
First things first: please excuse my English as i am not a native speaker. Thank you! 

We made a 2.5h trip with the catamaran (highly recommended!) to the Suba Dolphins with Vertigem Azul and found it awesome. The company has a high success rate of finding the dolphins (95%+) which are living in a group of 24 in the bay area. The ship is a modern catamaran (O Esperanza) for up to 80 passengers. On the nets in front you can enjoy the sun, the speed over water and the sight. The crew was very friendly and gave many information concerning the dolphins, in portuguese and in english. 

As a family with two kids (1 12y+) we paid 125€ and it was worth every cent.
reviews/13/title: Awesome trip to the dolphins of Setubal
reviews/14/text:
The boat left on time. The dolphins were quite south of Tróia, so it meant a 4 hour return trip. The weather was good, so that was a plus; fantastic catamaran.
The dolphins were really closed to the boat, but then dispersed a bit. We watched the dolphins for about 20 minutes - which I believe is quite long - and then the disappeared. No commentary, which would have improved the experience.
reviews/14/title: Dolphins were really closed to us
reviews/15/text:
We did the dolphins trip during the weekend. Everything was perfect including the very nice and professional crew. 
But I have to show my deep displeasure regarding one issue that should be review by Vertugem Azul management.
Almost at the end of the trip, an small boat approach the catamaran with 2 people that boarded into the catamaran for “SELLING BOLAS DE BERLIM (cake)”. Of course all the kids begging to  their parents  to buy it. The price was 3 EUR ( never saw it even in NY or Tokyo, or Miami beaches....). Of course it is another business for Vertigem Azul that abuses the time they have us onboarded to sell us products nothing to do with dolphins!

Hope they understand the “non sense” and the bad impression that they give with kind of “monkey business”
reviews/15/title: One very sad detail among an excellent morning
reviews/16/text:
Starting at Setubal port and with easy car parking right in front, you can find dolphins comunity almost 100%.
It’s a very nice experience for kids because they can see them and learn more about ecosystem they need to survive.
Even you can swimm in the sea for about 10 minutes
reviews/17/text: Our travel agent booked the 2:30 trip for us. I was happy to hear that once we spotted the dolphin pod we were only allowed to be near for 30 minutes. The boat was comfortable with plenty of seating. The dolphins were mostly spotted on the right side of the boat (where we were sitting) and some in the back. I had seen dolphins on boats before but they were much farther away. Having them 20-30 meters away was so cool.
reviews/18/text: A great company.  Totally professional.  They pride themselves on being ecological and abide by strict codes of conduct.  Beautiful boat.  Very good English.  Proper safety gear on board.  They can arrange transportation from Lisbon.  We had a wonderful afternoon with them and I highly recommend this company.
reviews/19/text: It is amazing how a successful company can, at the same time, set the rules of respect for animals. Thank you for the experience.

description: Sailing with the wind in harmony with nature along the beautiful coastline of Tróia & Arrábida or into the astonishing estuary of the Rio Sado. We want you to relax and enjoy like your are family & friends. Or you can be a real sailor setting the sails and steer the boat. Most often the dolphins come to swim along our sailing boat jumping & playing loving our bows without noisy dangerous engine.
name: Green Dolphin Sailing

reviews/0/text:
We had a beautiful afternoon at sea, Carmo and Peter took very good care of us.
This is the perfect afternoon excursion for families with children and friends. 
We were lucky and saw so many dolphins, it was incredible. Carmo spoilt us with drinks and snacks and took many pictures.
We highly recommend booking the green dolphin for an anfternoon.
reviews/0/title: Fun sailing trip for the family
reviews/1/text: One must go Dolphin watching when visiting Setúbal, on a good day it  is an experience not to be missed. These beautiful creatures sometimes with babies swim alongside the catamaran making it such a joy to appreciate nature at its best.
reviews/2/text:
What can I say apart from WOW !!

What amazing day we all had . 
Carmo and Peter are the perfect hosts . 

Great fun had by all on the boat . The dolphins were an emotional event for me as I’ve waited 44 years to see some .

My son George is 21 and my daughter India is 11 and they both loved it .

We also met new friends too ??

Thank you both for a great day
reviews/3/text:
Desta vez optamos por seguir o conselho dos nossos (amigos) Peter e Carmo e aproveitamos um dia completo a velezar no estuário do Sado.
Mal saimos de Setubal tivemos a sorte de avistar golfinhos depois visitar praias e locais secretos e isolados do rio sado .
O nosso almoço foi uma surpresa pois foi um achado pois fomos brindados com a oferta de pescadorfes locais para um petisco unico Ligueirão acabado de apanhar e no local onde o degustamos mais fantastico foi.
Depois existiu a oportunidade para o aniversariante e os amigos velejarem um pouco e fomos visitar as prais e falésias da arrabida que caiem sobre o sado.
Para terminar só a vontade de regressar logo que possivel.
O Peter (capitão) e a Carmo (imediato) são simplesmente fantásticos quer na sua procura constante em nos agradar e tentar que a nossa exepriencia foçe unica bem como numa proximidade de amizade quem tem com todos e que nos faz sentir em famila com eles também.
Um enorme Bem Haja e esperamos voltar o mais rápido possivel.
reviews/3/title: Aniversário do meu filho e passeio com muitos amigos
reviews/4/text:
Nous avons réservé 3h de catamaran, dans la lagune de Setubal. Non seulement l’accueil hyper sympa de Peter et son épouse nous ont toute suite mis à l’aise, mais aussi le fait d’être plongés direct dans un paysage magnifique.
Au bout d’une heure, nous tous confortablement installés dans de gros cousins , l’épouse de Peter nous propose un apéro Royal, les enfants n’en revenaient pas.  On s’arrête pour nager sur des bancs de sables, puis... ça y est, on voit les dauphins d’abord de très loin, on éteints les moteurs pour rejoindre la compagnie de dauphins à la voile pour ne pas les effrayer.  Il y avait même 2 bébés...
Malheureusement beaucoup de compagnies qui proposent des tours sont peu scrupuleux et s’approchent d’eux avec leurs gros moteurs , tout près.
Alors qu’ici, Green Dolphins le font dans le respect total des animaux.

Nous gardons un souvenir génial de cette aprèm, les enfants on adorés (même a 6 ans , ma fille était tout à fait à l’aise!).

Nous conseillons vivement ce tour en particulier (pour en avoir vu d’autres moins cool!!)
reviews/5/text:
Via google bij Green Dolphins terecht gekomen. We wilde graag met een wat kleiner/ persoonlijkere tocht mee waarbij respect voor de natuur/ dier ook belangrijk is.
Eerst direct contact gelegd met Kapitein Peter wat de beste dag/ tijd was komende dagen qua tocht en daarna rechtstreeks geboekt. Dit verliep lekker soepel. Via whatsapp tips gekregen voor gratis parkeren en de gps naar de boot.
Ontvangst en zeiltocht was fantastisch, alsof je met je eigen vrienden een dagdeel op pad bent. Je word ontvangen met koffie en een koekje(s) en ook later staat nog een drankje en snack op t menu. De boot is heerlijk, voldoende zitplek met kussens en ook een wc aan boord. Je hoeft je nergens druk om te maken en enkel en alleen te genieten.
Wij hadden het geluk een stuk of 15 a 20 dolfijnen rond de boot te hebben, wij kwamen ogen te kort.
Kortom zoek je een wat kleinschaliger en persoonlijke tocht, neem contact op met Kapitein Peter!  
Peter en Carmo heel erg bedankt voor de top dag!
reviews/6/text: Zeer gezelige namiddag. Kapitein Peter en zijn vriendin nemen je mee aan boord voor een aangename tocht.

reviews/0/text: We had the best experience ever in Portugal with the help of Alexandre Ferreira, our guide and now good friend! We definitely recommend him as the best guide to the most beautiful places in Portugal! Thanks to him, we had the most beautiful holiday here, in Portugal. We cannot wait to come back!
reviews/0/title: The best guide driver in Portugal
reviews/1/text: Paolo picked us up at LIS and took us to our hotel, offering us a concise and workable plan for our five day stay, and many excellent dining recommedations. We followed most of his suggestions, but used the Hop on Hop Off for touring the area, which he didn't think much of but we found useful in off season. He picked us up at Valverde Hotel and took us on a full day transfer/tour to Porto, The Yeatman. We recommend both hotels. On the way we took four side trips on his recommendations and they were excellent choices in the off season (November). Paolo is a wealth of knowledge of the local history and very personable and informative. At his recommendation we enjoyed a seafood lunch at a restaurant in Nazaré that was memorable. He is well known in the area and when he takes you somewhere you are made to feel like a VIP. We can't recommend him enough for those who want to be treated in a like manner.
reviews/1/title: LIS pickup with Paulo and full day tour/transfer to Porto.
reviews/2/text:
We are an Australian family with two teenage children. We travelled with Alex many times across almost a week including:

Porto to Lisbon. A Lisbon city tour. Lisbon to Evora. And Evora to Seville Spain. 

To say the service was excellent would be understating how much we enjoyed the travel. This was a new way of seeing the country for us and was a most efficient way of moving from place to place. 

Alex was an extremely safe driver, gave excellent touring suggestions and was well versed in giving us some important history lessons along the way. The vehicles used were roomy and comfortable. 

We truly missed Alex as we said goodbye and this made our family experience one to remember.
reviews/3/text: Alex was our driver for two days exploring Sintra, Lisbon and surrounding areas. He went over and above our expectations to ensure we experienced the best Portugal had to offer. Wonderful memories to take home and can’t recommend him highly enough.
reviews/4/text:
One word to describe this experience...
EXCELLENT
Thank you Paulo for two great tours!
Would definitely recommend ?
reviews/5/text:
We made a trip to Lisbon - Porto, in the company of the best driver/guide.

Tiago was very polite and kind!

In addition to the ideas we had in mind, thanks to his enormous knowledge, he gave us new options for stopping on the way to Porto.

Not to mention the best fish meal we had in Portugal.

When we return, we will choose again 2 Feel Portugal and Tiago if possible!
reviews/6/text:
We had 4 different tours with 2feelportugal recently. Each tour was customized to our interests and needs.Paulo handled every detail from arranging a winery visit to getting us the best gelato! We just loved spending the days with him giving us a true taste of the country. 
When we return Paulo will be the first to know! Couldn't be happier with this company.
reviews/7/text: Customized trip from Cascais to Evora was great. Toured the old City, saw the Churches, Roman ruins, and had a marvelous lunch. Then toured a cork factory (fascinating) and lastly a vineyard to taste wonderful Portuguese wine.
reviews/8/text:
Nesta viagem decidimos percorrer o país de Lisboa até Braga/ Guimarães. Uma vez que a família é grande e estamos radicados na Suiça há muito tempo, optamos por os serviços da 2FeelPortugal.
A forma como fomos tratados foi mais como se de família se tratasse do que um contrato comercial.... O Paulo foi de uma simpatia e sensibilidade sensacionais. Levou-nos a visitar Sintra, a Regaleira e Lisboa. Depois levou-nos a Óbidos e Fátima e, de seguida a Coimbra.
Depois Aveiro, Porto, Braga e Guimarães. Para além do profissionalismo, sempre nos mimou com pequenas surpresas dos locais visitados.
No Porto, Braga, Guimarães e Douro tivemos o acompanhamento da Júlia com quem também nos relacionamos de imediato dada a sua simpatia. Adorámos ouvir as histórias que contou sobre estes locais..... Será uma experiência a repetir e a divulgar em Basel....
reviews/9/text: Foi realmente uma experiência fantástica, onde tudo correu como planeado e mais ! Desde os transfers por nós contratados para apanhar cerca de 20 pessoas com voos diferentes no aeroporto de lisboa e o regresso dos mesmos, city tour pedestre em lisboa fantástico dividido por cerca de 3 grupos onde se adaptaram a realidade dos grupos, visita ao palácio da Pena com áudio guias , almoços jantares enfim , do melhor mesmo . Parabéns !
reviews/10/text: Fizemos (minha mãe e eu) um passeio de um dia a Sintra e Cascais e também um  passeio de um dia a Évora , ambos com Paulo, da 2feel,  e foi uma experiência muito agradável. Paulo é extremamente gentil e educado e fez de tudo para que nosso passeio fosse bem aproveitado. Em Évora fomos a uma quinta e fizemos degustação de azeite, com almoço caseiro. Divino!! Depois fomos a Monsaraz, cidade medieval lindíssima. Recomendo muito a empresa e a companhia de Paulo como guia (um dos sócios).
